---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { buildBreadcrumbJsonLd } from '../lib/seo';

const breadcrumb = buildBreadcrumbJsonLd([
  { name: 'Home', path: '/' }, { name: 'Privacy Policy', path: '/privacy' },
]);
---
<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy | ToolOrbit" description="ToolOrbit's privacy policy. Most tools run entirely client-side - your files never leave your device." canonicalPath="/privacy" jsonLd={[breadcrumb]}>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-base-50 mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-base-500 mb-10">Last updated: June 28, 2026</p>
    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none prose-headings:font-display prose-headings:text-base-50 prose-p:text-base-300 prose-a:text-interactive prose-li:text-base-300 prose-strong:text-base-100">
      <h2>The short version</h2>
      <p>Most tools on ToolOrbit run entirely in your browser. Your files, text, and data are processed locally and are never sent to our servers. The only data we collect is what you explicitly provide when creating an account (name and email) and aggregate analytics via Cloudflare Web Analytics.</p>

      <h2>Client-side processing</h2>
      <p>PDF tools, image tools, text tools, developer tools, and calculators all run client-side using JavaScript in your browser tab. When you upload a PDF or image to these tools, the file is read into browser memory, processed, and the output is offered for download - without any network request for the file data itself.</p>

      <h2>Account data (optional)</h2>
      <p>If you create an account using Google or GitHub Sign-In, we store:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your name and email address as provided by your OAuth provider</li>
        <li>A profile image URL from your OAuth provider</li>
        <li>The tools you save as favorites (tool slugs only - not file content)</li>
        <li>The slugs of tools you have recently used (stored client-side, no file content)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This data is stored in a Cloudflare D1 database accessible only to ToolOrbit. You can delete your account at any time from the dashboard, which deletes all associated data.</p>

      <h2>Analytics</h2>
      <p>We use Cloudflare Web Analytics, which is cookieless and privacy-preserving. It collects aggregate page view counts and performance metrics without tracking individual users or storing personally identifiable information. No third-party analytics scripts are loaded.</p>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>Session cookies are set only if you create an account and log in. A theme preference token is stored in localStorage. No advertising cookies or third-party tracking cookies are used.</p>

      <h2>Data sharing</h2>
      <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties. The only third-party services with access to any user data are Cloudflare (infrastructure) and Google/GitHub (OAuth - only during the sign-in flow, and only the data they provide us during that flow).</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions about this policy: <a href="mailto:tanviroyon001@gmail.com">tanviroyon001@gmail.com</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
